'''捆綁式付款'''（{{lang-en|Bundled payment}}）"是針對所定義的護理事件產生的費用，給予[[醫療衛生提供者|醫療衛生提供者]]（例如醫院和醫生）的補償。" <ref name="Cromwell-1997">{{Cite journal | vauthors = Cromwell J, Dayhoff DA, Thoumaian AH | title = Cost savings and physician responses to global bundled payments for Medicare heart bypass surgery | journal = Health Care Financ Rev | volume = 19 | issue = 1 | pages = 41–57 | year = 1997 | url = http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m0795/is_n1_v19/ai_20750869/ | pmid = 10180001 | pmc = 4194487 | access-date = 2020-09-11 | archive-date = 2012-01-18 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120118052719/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m0795/is_n1_v19/ai_20750869/ | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="Miller-2008">{{Cite news | url= http://managedhealthcareexecutive.modernmedicine.com/mhe/Cover+Article/Package-pricing-Geisingers-new-model-holds-the-pro/ArticleStandard/Article/detail/522495 | author= Miller J | title= Package pricing: Geisinger's new model holds the promise of aligning payment with optimal care | newspaper= Managed Healthcare Executive | date= 1 June 2008 | accessdate= 2010-03-11 | archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20101001223614/http://managedhealthcareexecutive.modernmedicine.com/mhe/Cover+Article/Package-pricing-Geisingers-new-model-holds-the-pro/ArticleStandard/Article/detail/522495 | archive-date= 2010-10-01 | url-status= dead }}</ref><ref name="MA-2009a">{{Cite web |url= http://www.mass.gov/Eeohhs2/docs/dhcfp/pc/Final_Report/Appendix%20C%20-%20Payment%20Models%20&%20Comp%20Strategies.pdf |author= Commonwealth of Massachusetts, Special Commission on the Health Care Payment System |title= Recommendations of the Special Commission on the Health Care Payment System. Appendix C: memos on basic payment models and complementary payment-related strategies |date= 16 July 2009 |accessdate= 2010-03-11 |archive-date= 2011-06-04 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20110604212835/http://www.mass.gov/Eeohhs2/docs/dhcfp/pc/Final_Report/Appendix%20C%20-%20Payment%20Models%20%26%20Comp%20Strategies.pdf |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref name="Satin-2009">{{Cite journal|date=2009|title=Performance-based bundled payments: potential benefits and burdens|url=https://p4presearch.dl.umn.edu/sites/g/files/pua991/f/media/mn_med_bundles_special_report_-_satin.pdf|journal=Minn Med|volume=92|issue=10|pages=33–5|doi=|pmid=19916270|access-date=|via=|vauthors=Satin DJ, Miles J|archive-date=2017-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202001203/https://p4presearch.dl.umn.edu/sites/g/files/pua991/f/media/mn_med_bundles_special_report_-_satin.pdf|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name="Miller-2009">{{Cite journal | author = Miller HD | title = From volume to value: better ways to pay for health care | journal = Health Aff (Millwood) | volume = 28 | issue = 5 | pages = 1418–28 | year = 2009 | doi = 10.1377/hlthaff.28.5.1418 | url = http://healthaff.highwire.org/cgi/content/full/28/5/1418 | pmid = 19738259 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://archive.is/20130415002809/http://healthaff.highwire.org/cgi/content/full/28/5/1418 | archivedate = 2013-04-15 }}</ref>這種支付方式算是介於[[按服務收費|按服務收費]]（根據醫療服務提供者的各項服務，逐項付費）和[[論人計酬付費|論人計酬付費]]（向患者的服務提供者作固定"總價"支付，不論提供多少服務）兩者之間的"中間地帶"，這種支付方式的概念是付款者和提供者應共同承擔風險。<ref name="RAND-2009">{{Cite web|url= http://www.randcompare.org/policy-options/bundled-payment|author= RAND Corporation|title= Overview of bundled payment|accessdate= 2010-03-11|archive-date= 2010-12-29|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20101229210924/http://www.randcompare.org/policy-options/bundled-payment|dead-url= no}}</ref>在美國進行的醫療衛生改革辯論中，捆綁式付款的方式被提出，目的在降低醫療衛生成本，這情況在維基百科中[[歐巴馬執政期間提出的醫療改革方案|歐巴馬執政期間提出的醫療改革方案]]和[[患者保護與平價醫療法案|患者保護與平價醫療法案]]兩篇文章中均有描述。<ref name="Obama-2009a">{{Cite web |url= http://www.whitehouse.gov/the_press_office/Remarks-by-the-President-to-the-Annual-Conference-of-the-American-Medical-Association |title= Remarks by the President at the annual conference of the American Medical Association |author= Obama B |date= 15 June 2009 |accessdate= 2010-03-11 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20100313084300/http://www.whitehouse.gov/the_press_office/Remarks-by-the-President-to-the-Annual-Conference-of-the-American-Medical-Association/ |archive-date= 2010-03-13 |url-status= dead }}</ref>商業保險公司對捆綁式付款也表達興趣，希望藉此降低成本。<ref name=cg/>根據一份在2012年的報告，美國醫療衛生費用的報銷裡面，接近有三分之一會使用到某種程度的捆綁式付款方法。<ref name=cg3>{{cite web| url=http://www.thecamdengroup.com/thought-leadership/top-ten/top-10-considerations-for-clinical-service-line-leaders/| title=Top 10 Considerations for Clinical Service Line Leaders| date=July 2012| author=Deirdre Baggot| publisher=GE Healthcare Camden Group| access-date=June 13, 2016| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160617055338/http://www.thecamdengroup.com/thought-leadership/top-ten/top-10-considerations-for-clinical-service-line-leaders/| archive-date=June 17, 2016| url-status=dead}}</ref>

==不同的英文名稱==
捆綁式付款的英文名稱也可寫作：'''episode-based payment''', '''episode payment''', '''episode-of-care payment''', '''case rate''', '''evidence-based case rate''', '''global bundled payment''', '''global payment''', '''package pricing''', 或者 '''packaged pricing'''.
 
==歷史==
在1980年代中期，人們認為根據[[聯邦醫療保險|聯邦醫療保險]]（Medicare）的{{link-en|診斷相關組|Diagnosis-related group}}（醫院病情分類）所設計的[[預期付款系統|預期付款系統]]，可能會導致醫院為省錢，而提前把患者送往出院後的護理單位（例如如{{link-en|療養院|Nursing home}}）。<ref name="Neu-1986">{{Cite web |url=http://www.rand.org/pubs/reports/2009/R3335.pdf |title=Extending the Medicare prospective payment system to posthospital care. Planning a demonstration |vauthors=Neu CR, Palmer A, Henry DP, Olson GT, Harrison S |date=May 1986 |publisher=RAND Corporation |location=Santa Monica, CA |accessdate=2010-03-11 |archive-date=2012-10-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121004045352/http://www.rand.org/pubs/reports/2009/R3335.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref> 因此有建議Medicare用捆綁的方式把費用共同支付給醫院和出院後護理機構； <ref name="Neu-1986"/>雖然這個構想的分析良好，<ref name="Welch-1998">{{Cite journal | author = Welch WP | title = Bundled Medicare payment for acute and postacute care | journal = Health Aff (Millwood) | volume = 17 | issue = 6 | pages = 69–81 | year = 1998 | url = http://healthaff.highwire.org/cgi/reprint/17/6/69.pdf | pmid = 9916356 | doi = 10.1377/hlthaff.17.6.69 }}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref name="CBO-2008">{{Cite book |title= Budget options. Volume I. Health care |chapter= Chapter 5. The quality and efficiency of health care. Option 30. Bundle payments for hospital care and post-acute care |author= Congressional Budget Office |date= December 2008 |publisher= Congress of the United States |location= Washington, DC |pages= 62–63 |chapter-url= http://www.cbo.gov/ftpdocs/99xx/doc9925/12-18-HealthOptions.pdf |accessdate= 2010-03-11 |archive-date= 2012-02-17 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20120217164832/http://www.cbo.gov/ftpdocs/99xx/doc9925/12-18-HealthOptions.pdf |dead-url= no }}</ref>到2009年時仍未實施。<ref name="PostAcute-2009">{{Cite web|url=http://www.post-acute.org/bundling/Bundling%20Report%20V15.pdf|title=Bundling payment for post-acute care: building blocks and policy options|author=Center for Post-acute Studies|year=2009|publisher=National Rehabilitation Hospital|location=Washington, DC|accessdate=2010-03-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727182953/http://www.post-acute.org/bundling/Bundling%20Report%20V15.pdf|archive-date=2011-07-27|url-status=dead}}</ref>
 
===1980到1990年代===
捆綁式付款始於1984年，在{{link-en|德克薩斯心臟醫學中心|Texas Heart Institute}}創始人{{link-en|Denton Cooley|Denton Cooley}}的指導之下，開始對醫院本身和醫師在心血管外科的服務收取固定費用。<ref name="Miller-2009"/><ref name="Edmonds-1995">{{Cite journal|vauthors=Edmonds C, Hallman GL | title = CardioVascular Care Providers. A pioneer in bundled services, shared risk, and single payment | journal = Tex Heart Inst J | volume = 22 | issue = 1 | pages = 72–6 | year = 1995 | pmid = 7787473 | pmc=325213}}</ref>來自院內的文章發表者聲稱，這種收費方法不但能降低成本，同時"也維持良好品質的護理"（1985年，這所醫院進行的[[冠狀動脈旁路移植|心臟繞道手術]]的固定費用為13,800美元，而Medicare的平均報銷金額為24,588美元）。<ref name="Edmonds-1995"/>
 
1987年和1989年之間，另有一種捆綁式付款的早期案例，涉及一位[[骨外科|骨外科]]醫生，一間教學醫院（{{link-en|McLaren Greater Lansinghospital|McLaren Greater Lansinghospital}}，之前名稱為Ingham Regional Medical Center），以及一所[[健康維護組織|健康維護組織]]（HMO），三者都在[[密西根州|密西根州]]。<ref name="Miller-2009"/><ref name="Johnson-1994">{{Cite journal|vauthors=Johnson LL, Becker RL | title = An alternative health-care reimbursement system -- application of arthroscopy and financial warranty: results of a 2-year pilot study | journal = Arthroscopy | volume = 10 | issue = 4 | pages = 462–70; discussion 471–2 | year = 1994 | doi = 10.1016/S0749-8063(05)80200-2 | url = http://www.arthroscopyjournal.org/article/S0749-8063%2805%2980200-2/abstract | pmid = 7945644}}</ref>HMO 把111名患者轉介給這位骨外科醫生，讓他進行手術；醫生對每位患者免費做評估。<ref name="Johnson-1994"/>醫生和醫院對所做的每次[[關節鏡|關節鏡]]手術均收取事先談定的費用，並提供為期兩年的[[保用證|保固]]，承諾會負擔手術後的任何費用，HMO不用負擔（結果是做了四次免費的重做手術）。<ref name="Johnson-1994"/>在這種安排下，"各方都在經濟上受益"：HMO支付193,000美元，而非預計的318,538美元；醫院收到96,500美元，而非預計的84,892美元；並且外科醫生和他的同事得到96,500美元，而非預計的51,877美元。<ref name="Johnson-1994"/>
 
1991年，在全美有四所醫院啟動一項"Medicare參與心臟繞道手術中心示範"的活動。1993年，又有三所醫院加入，這項活動在1996年結束。<ref name="Cromwell-1997"/><ref name="Cromwell-1998">{{Cite web |url=http://www.cms.hhs.gov/DemoProjectsEvalRpts/downloads/Medicare_Heart_Bypass_Executive_Summary.pdf |title=Medicare Participating Heart Bypass Demonstration. Executive summary. Final report |vauthors=Cromwell J, Dayhoff DA, McCall NT, Subramanian S, Freitas RC, Hart RJ, Caswell C, Stason W |date=1998-07-24 |publisher=Health Economics Research, Inc |location=Waltham, MA |accessdate=2010-03-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091122094610/http://www.cms.hhs.gov/DemoProjectsEvalRpts/downloads/Medicare_Heart_Bypass_Executive_Summary.pdf |archive-date=2009-11-22 |url-status=dead }}</ref>在示範中，Medicare向醫院和醫師支付的是通用型手術住院費用（包括任何相關的重新住院費用）。<ref name="Cromwell-1997"/>對於這項活動所發表的評估如下：
 
*在1997年做的的分析，估計在1991年到1993年間，最早加入活動的四家醫院，為Medicare受益人所做的心臟繞道手術的總支出是1.108億美元，但報銷方式的變化，為Medicare節省1,531萬美元，為Medicare受益人以及提供補充保險的私人保險公司節省184萬美元，總共節省1,720萬美元（15.5％）。<ref name="Cromwell-1997"/>在節省的總數裡面，85％-93％是住院費用，另外6％-11％是院後的護理；而且"品質並沒有降低"。<ref name="Cromwell-1997"/>
*1998年向{{link-en|聯邦醫療保險和聯邦醫療補助服務中心|Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services}}（CMS）的前身醫療衛生籌資管理局（Health Care Financing Administration）提出的一份報告指出，在這項示範項目執行的的五年中，總共七家醫院為Medicare受益人的心臟繞道手術支出為4.38億美元，但報銷方式的變化為Medicare節省4,230萬美元，為Medicare受益人以及補充保險公司節省790萬美元，總共節省5,030萬美元（11.5％）。<ref name="Cromwell-1998"/>此外，在控制患者危險因素方面，示範醫院在這段期間的住院死亡率有所下降。<ref name="Cromwell-1998"/>這個項目的缺點有在收費和催討方面碰到困難。<ref name="Cromwell-1998"/>
*在2001年有篇論文，對檢查最早參加的四家醫院中的三家，就它們擁有的"細部成本"數據作檢驗，確定"成本降低，主要來自加護病房護理、常規護理、藥品、和導管室。" <ref name="Liu-2001">{{Cite journal|vauthors=Liu CF, Subramanian S, Cromwell J | title = Impact of global bundled payments on hospital costs of coronary artery bypass grafting |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-health-care-finance_summer-2001_27_4/page/39 | journal = J Health Care Finance | volume = 27 | issue = 4 | pages = 39–54 | year = 2001 | pmid = 11434712 }}</ref>
 
===2000年代===
到2001年，當時被稱為"case rates for episodes of illness"的捆綁式付款，被認為是"混合式付款法"（由追溯性和預期性付款兩者的結合）的一種類型，同時還包括"[[論人計酬支付|論人計酬支付]]加上[[按服務收費|按服務收費]]"和"按服務收費專項預算，或者是專科醫生的論人計酬支付的專項預算。"<ref name="Robinson-2001">{{Cite journal | author = Robinson JC | title = Theory and practice in the design of physician payment incentives | journal = Milbank Q | volume = 79 | issue = 2 | pages = 149–77 | year = 2001 | url = http://www.milbank.org/quarterly/7902feat.html | pmid = 11439463 | pmc = 2751195 | doi = 10.1111/1468-0009.00202 | access-date = 2020-09-11 | archive-date = 2012-03-01 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120301181919/http://www.milbank.org/quarterly/7902feat.html | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/11066668/</ref>在隨後的幾年中，有其他混合付款方式被提出，例如"綜合護理付款（comprehensive care payment）"、<ref name="Miller-2009"/> "綜合護理綜合付款（comprehensive payment for comprehensive care）"，<ref name="Goroll-2007">{{Cite journal|vauthors=Goroll AH, Berenson RA, Schoenbaum SC, Gardner LB | title = Fundamental reform of payment for adult primary care: comprehensive payment for comprehensive care | journal = J Gen Intern Med | volume = 22 | issue = 3 | pages = 410–5 | year = 2007 | doi = 10.1007/s11606-006-0083-2 | pmid=17356977 | pmc=1824766}}</ref>、和"全面慢性病護理（complete chronic care）"<ref name="HC4HR-2009">{{Cite web |url= http://newamerica.net/files/DeliverySystemWhitePaper.pdf |title= Realigning U.S. health care incentives to better serve patients and taxpayers |author= Health CEOs for Health Reform |date= 12 June 2009 |location= Washington, DC |publisher= New America Foundation |accessdate= 2010-03-13 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20110428210757/http://www.newamerica.net/files/DeliverySystemWhitePaper.pdf |archive-date= 28 April 2011 |url-status= dead }}</ref>，除了用於支付治療疾病的費用之外，還包括支付維持人們健康的費用。
 
在2003年，由醫學博士Deirdre Baggot <ref>https://www.linkedin.com/in/deirdrebaggot</ref>主持，在[[丹佛|丹佛]]的{{link-en|聖約瑟夫醫院|Saint Joseph Hospital (Denver, Colorado)}}舉行[[急性|急性]]病症護理（ACE）示範項目。ACE是根據{《{{le|2008年Medicare改善患者和醫療機構法案|Medicare Improvements for Patients and Providers Act of 2008}}》辦理，把Medicare的A部分和B部分相關的護理作捆綁式支付。<ref name=mh/>
 
在2006年至2007年間，一所[[醫療衛生提供者|醫療衛生提供者]]{{link-en|Geisinger醫療系統|Geisinger Health System}}在心臟繞道手術上，測試一個稱為"ProvenCare"的模式，其中包括[[最佳實踐|最佳實踐]]，患者參與，以及"把手術前、住院、和手術後90天內再入院治療等費用…………集中為一個固定的價格。" <ref name="Casale-2007">{{Cite journal|vauthors=Casale AS, Paulus RA, Selna MJ, Doll MC, Bothe AE Jr, McKinley KE, Berry SA, Davis DE, Gilfillan RJ, Hamory BH, Steele GD Jr |title='ProvenCare<sup>SM</sup>': a provider-driven pay-for-performance program for acute episodic cardiac surgical care |journal=Ann Surg |volume=246 |issue=4 |pages=613–21; discussion 621–3 |year=2007 |doi=10.1097/SLA.0b013e318155a996 |url=http://www.geisinger.org/provencare/as_pc.pdf |pmid=17893498 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100827070337/http://www.geisinger.org/provencare/as_pc.pdf |archivedate=2010-08-27 }}</ref>這個計劃在2007年中期受到各方關注，其中包括有刊載在《[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]》 <ref name="Abelson-2009">{{Cite news |title= In bid for better care, surgery with a warranty |author= Abelson R |newspaper= The New York Times |date= 17 May 2007 |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2007/05/17/business/17quality.html |accessdate= 2010-03-11 |archive-date= 2020-11-09 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201109030723/http://www.nytimes.com/2007/05/17/business/17quality.html |dead-url= no }}</ref>和《[[新英格蘭醫學雜誌|新英格蘭醫學雜誌]]》 <ref name="Lee-2007">{{Cite journal|author=Lee TH |title=Pay for performance, version 2.0? |journal=N Engl J Med |volume=357 |issue=6 |pages=531–3 |year=2007 |doi=10.1056/NEJMp078124 |url=http://www.geisinger.org/provencare/nejm_pc.pdf |pmid=17687128 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100827070457/http://www.geisinger.org/provencare/nejm_pc.pdf |archivedate=2010-08-27 }}</ref>的報導。在2007年末發布的一項評估顯示，在2005年，接受" ProvenCare"治療的117例患者與接受傳統方式治療的137例患者相比，總住院時間明顯縮短（住院費用節省5％），出院回家的機會更高，再入院率更低。<ref name="Casale-2007"/>
 
美國最大專注在健康的慈善事業{{link-en|羅伯特·伍德·約翰遜基金會|Robert Wood Johnson Foundatio}}從2007年開始，撥款給捆綁式項目-簡稱為PROMETHEUS計劃（全名Provider payment Reform for Outcomes, Margins, Evidence, Transparency, Hassle-reduction, Excellence, Understandability and Sustainability，第一個英文字母的縮寫）。<ref name="Gosfield-2007">{{Cite web |url= http://www.rwjf.org/files/research/makingitreal.pdf |title= Making PROMETHEUS payment rates real: ya' gotta start somewhere |author= Gosfield AG |date= June 2008 |location= Princeton, NJ |publisher= Robert Wood Johnson Foundation |accessdate= 2010-03-13 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20110927140049/http://www.rwjf.org/files/research/makingitreal.pdf |archive-date= 2011-09-27 |url-status= dead }}</ref>，這個項目在{{le|聯邦基金會|Commonwealth Fund}}的支持下，針對各種病症制定"包含證據的病例比率"，並根據患者疾病的嚴重程度和複雜程度作調整。<ref name="deBrantes-2007">{{Cite web |url= http://www.commonwealthfund.org/usr_doc/deBrantes_evidence-informedcaserates_1022.pdf |title= Evidence-informed case rates: a new health care payment model |vauthors= de Brantes F, Camillus JA |date= April 2007 |location= Washington, DC |publisher= The Commonwealth Fund |accessdate= 2010-03-13 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20110720063141/http://www.commonwealthfund.org/usr_doc/deBrantes_evidence-informedcaserates_1022.pdf |archive-date= 2011-07-20 |url-status= dead }}</ref><ref name="deBrantes-2009">{{Cite journal|vauthors=de Brantes F, Rosenthal MB, Painter M | title = Building a bridge from fragmentation to accountability--the Prometheus Payment model | journal = N Engl J Med | volume = 361 | issue = 11 | pages = 1033–6 | year = 2009 | doi = 10.1056/NEJMp0906121 | pmid = 19692682 }}</ref><ref name="PROMETHEUS">{{Cite web |url= http://www.prometheuspayment.org/mission/funding.htm |title= Our funding |author= Prometheus Payment, Inc |accessdate= 2010-03-13 |archive-url= https://archive.is/20080820081742/http://www.prometheuspayment.org/mission/funding.htm |archive-date= 2008-08-20 |url-status= dead }}</ref>"包含證據的病例比率"被用來制定護理預算。<ref name="deBrantes-2009"/>如果醫療衛生提供者的實際季度支出低於預算，則會獲得額外獎金；如果實際季度支出超出預算，付款將被部分扣減。<ref name="deBrantes-2009"/>這個項目在三個試點進行測試，在2011年結束。<ref name="deBrantes-2009"/><ref name="PROMETHEUS"/>這個項目的結果是以失敗收場。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://pnhp.org/news/the-prometheus-bundled-payment-experiment/ |title=存档副本 |access-date=2020-09-11 |archive-date=2021-02-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210223204602/https://pnhp.org/news/the-prometheus-bundled-payment-experiment/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

在2008年中期，{{link-en|Medicare付款諮詢委員會|Medicare Payment Advisory Commission}}沿著"捆綁式付款的路徑"提出幾項建議。<ref name="MedPAC-2008">{{Cite book |title= Report to the Congress: reforming the delivery system |chapter= Chapter 4. A path to bundled payment around a hospitalization |author= Medicare Payment Advisory Commission |date= June 2008 |publisher= Medicare Payment Advisory Commission |location= Washington, DC |pages= 80–103 |chapter-url= http://www.medpac.gov/documents/Jun08_EntireReport.pdf |accessdate= 2010-03-11 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20080916091232/http://www.medpac.gov/documents/Jun08_EntireReport.pdf |archive-date= 2008-09-16 |url-status= dead }}</ref><ref name="Hackbarth-2008">{{Cite journal|vauthors=Hackbarth G, Reischauer R, Mutti A |title=Collective accountability for medical care--toward bundled Medicare payments |journal=N Engl J Med |volume=359 |issue=1 |pages=3–5 |year=2008 |doi=10.1056/NEJMp0803749 |url=http://www.ipalc.org/Accountable_Care_Organizations/Collective%20Accountability%20for%20Medical%20Care--Toward%20Bundled%20Medicare%20Payments%20(NEJM%207-3-2008).pdf |pmid=18596270 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110726184934/http://www.ipalc.org/Accountable_Care_Organizations/Collective%20Accountability%20for%20Medical%20Care--Toward%20Bundled%20Medicare%20Payments%20%28NEJM%207-3-2008%29.pdf |archivedate=2011-07-26 }}</ref> 其中一項是建議[[美國衛生和公共服務部|美國衛生和公共服務部]]（HHS）部長研究像是"虛擬捆綁"的方法（提供者仍然根據個別服務收費，但也根據實際支出水準而受到獎勵或者懲罰）。<ref name="MedPAC-2008"/>此外，有個建立試點計劃的提議，"以測試針對住院相關的特定服務，實施實際捆綁式付款的可行性。" <ref name="MedPAC-2008"/>
 
就在付款諮詢委員會報告發布之前，CMS宣布一項"Medicare急性病症護理示範"項目，用於某些[[心血管疾病|心血管疾病]]和[[骨外科|骨外科]]手術費的捆綁式付款。<ref name="Alexander-2008">{{Cite journal | author = Alexander J | title = Payment by episode: momentum building for bundling? | journal = Healthc Financ Manage | volume = 62 | issue = 7 | pages = 40–1 | year = 2008 | url = http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m3257/is_7_62/ai_n28072661/ | pmid = 18683410 | access-date = 2020-09-11 | archive-date = 2012-07-06 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120706104125/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m3257/is_7_62/ai_n28072661/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>這項付款僅包括醫院和醫師費用，不包括出院後護理；到2009年，這個項目選擇[[科羅拉多州|科羅拉多州]]、[[新墨西哥州|新墨西哥州]]、[[奧克拉荷馬州|奧克拉荷馬州]]、和[[德克薩斯州|德克薩斯州]]五地辦理。<ref name="Alexander-2008">{{Cite journal| author = Alexander J | title = Payment by episode: momentum building for bundling? | journal = Healthc Financ Manage | volume = 62 | issue = 7 | pages = 40–1 | year = 2008 | url = http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m3257/is_7_62/ai_n28072661/ | pmid = 18683410 }}</ref>執行這個項目，醫院為選定的療程提供 1％到6％的Medicare折扣，而Medicare的受益人將獲得250至1,157美元的參與治療獎勵。<ref name="Galewitz-2009">{{Cite news |title= Can 'bundled' payments help slash health costs? |author= Galewitz P |url= https://www.usatoday.com/news/health/2009-10-25-bundle-payments_N.htm |newspaper= USA Today |date= 26 October 2009 |access-date= 2010-03-11 |archive-date= 2011-02-20 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20110220131241/http://www.usatoday.com/news/health/2009-10-25-bundle-payments_N.htm |dead-url= no }}</ref>

[[美國參議院財政委員會|美國參議院財政委員會]]主席[[馬克斯·博卡斯|馬克斯·博卡斯]]（民主黨籍）在2008年11月發布的[[白皮書|白皮書]]中，把 Medicare的捆綁式付款作為主打特點。<ref name="Goldstein-2009">{{Cite news |title= Medicare-payment fix weighed |author= Goldstein J |newspaper= Wall Street Journal |date= 30 January 2009 |url= https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB123327916525131681 |accessdate= 2010-03-11 |archive-date= 2020-10-01 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201001084214/https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB123327916525131681 |dead-url= no }}</ref>白皮書建議把Medicare急性病症護理示範項目"擴展到其他地點"，"如果某些其他的臨床狀況條件符合的話，也把措施用在這些情況之上"和"出院後的服務也包括在內"。<ref name="Baucus-2008">{{Cite web|url=http://finance.senate.gov/healthreform2009/finalwhitepaper.pdf |title=Call to action. Health reform 2009 |author=Baucus M |date=12 November 2008 |accessdate=2010-03-11 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100105223934/http://finance.senate.gov/healthreform2009/finalwhitepaper.pdf |archivedate=January 5, 2010 }}</ref>
 
截至2008年，Geisinger醫療系統的ProvenCare計劃"引起Medicare官員和其他業界頂尖公司的興趣"<ref name="Miller-2008"/>，並且已經擴展到，或這正擴展到{{link-en|髖關節置換術|Hip replacement }}、[[白內障手術|白內障手術]]、[[經皮冠狀動脈介入治療|氣球擴張術}}、[[代謝手術]]、[[下背痛|下背痛]]手術、和[[妊娠|妊娠]]護理。<ref name="Paulus-2008">{{Cite journal | vauthors = Paulus RA, Davis K, Steele GD | title = Continuous innovation in health care: implications of the Geisinger experience | journal = Health Aff (Millwood) | volume = 27 | issue = 5 | pages = 1235–45 | year = 2008 | doi = 10.1377/hlthaff.27.5.1235 | url = http://www.cga.ct.gov/PH/PrimaryCare/Docs/Geisinger%20Experience%20Medical%20Homes%20reduce%20hospitalizations.pdf | pmid = 18780906 | access-date = 2010-03-16 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100528003335/http://www.cga.ct.gov/ph/PrimaryCare/Docs/Geisinger%20Experience%20Medical%20Homes%20reduce%20hospitalizations.pdf | archive-date = 2010-05-28 | url-status = dead }}</ref>2009年，當新聞媒體報導稱Geisinger醫療系統 的模式就是[[巴拉克·歐巴馬|歐巴馬]]總統提出的醫療改革的模式<ref name="Connolly-2009">{{Cite news |title=For this health system, less is more. Program that guarantees doing things right the first time, for flat fee, pays off |author=Connolly C |newspaper=Washington Post |date=31 March 2009 |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/03/30/AR2009033003008.html |accessdate=2010-03-11 |archive-date=2021-01-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210131081140/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/03/30/AR2009033003008.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，以及歐巴馬本人在兩次演講中提到這個機構時，人們對Geisinger醫療系統就越感到興趣。<ref name="Obama-2009a"/><ref name="Obama-2009b">{{Cite web |url= http://www.whitehouse.gov/the_press_office/Remarks-by-the-President-in-Town-Hall-Meeting-on-Health-Care-in-Green-Bay-Wisconsin/ |title= Remarks by the President in towh (sic) hall meeting on health care |author= Obama B |date= 11 June 2009 |accessdate= 2010-03-11 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20100313103959/http://www.whitehouse.gov/the_press_office/Remarks-by-the-President-in-Town-Hall-Meeting-on-Health-Care-in-Green-Bay-Wisconsin/ |archive-date= 2010-03-13 |url-status= dead }}</ref>
 
2009年7月，[[麻薩諸塞州|麻薩諸塞州]]醫療衛生支付系統特別委員會對基於疾病發作醫療的支付（即捆綁式支付）和"通用支付"兩者定義作區分，通用支付是 "對患者在治療期間所支付的固定的金額……這種方式會讓提供者（在患者發作和治療方面）都面臨財務上的風險。" <ref name="MA-2009a"/>委員會建議麻薩諸塞州對於通用支付"應進行調整，以獎勵醫療機構提供容易獲得以及優質的醫療服務"（不是捆綁式付款）。<ref name="MA-2009b">{{Cite web|url= http://www.mass.gov/Eeohhs2/docs/dhcfp/pc/Final_Report/Final_Report.pdf|author= Commonwealth of Massachusetts, Special Commission on the Health Care Payment System|title= Recommendations of the Special Commission on the Health Care Payment System|date= 16 July 2009|accessdate= 2010-03-11|archive-date= 2011-10-25|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20111025081128/http://www.mass.gov/Eeohhs2/docs/dhcfp/pc/Final_Report/Final_Report.pdf|dead-url= no}}</ref>當初選擇通用支付的原因，是它可減少患者在麻州使用護理的次數，還有麻州以往曾使用過這種方法的緣故。<ref name="MA-2009b"/>
 
===患者保護與平價醫療法案通過之後===
在2010年，《[[患者保護與平價醫療法案|患者保護與平價醫療法案]]（PPACA）》以及《{{link-en|眾議院平價醫療法案|Affordable Health Care for America Act}}》 <ref name="KFF">{{Cite web |url= http://www.kff.org/healthreform/upload/housesenatebill_final.pdf |title= Side-by-side comparison of major health care reform proposals |author= Henry J. Kaiser Family Foundation |date= 24 February 2010 |publisher= Henry J. Kaiser Family Foundation |location= Menlo Park, CA |accessdate= 2010-03-13 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20100320211420/http://www.kff.org/healthreform/upload/housesenatebill_final.pdf |archive-date= 2010-03-20 |url-status= dead }}</ref>中都包含有捆綁式付款的規定。PPACA從2013年開始設立Medicare保險試點計劃，並預備從2016年起進行擴展，<ref>Bundled Payments – Medicare Pilot Program. Health Reform GPS: a Joint Project of the George Washington University and the Robert Wood Johnson Foundation. http://healthreformgps.org/resources/bundled-payments-%E2%80%93-medicare-pilot-program/ {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100514083323/http://www.healthreformgps.org/resources/bundled-payments-%E2%80%93-medicare-pilot-program/ |date=2010-05-14 }}.</ref>與當初歐巴馬的提議一致。<ref name="KFF"/>而眾議院的法案要求設立"一項改革 Medicare急性病症出院後服務在內的計劃，包括捆綁式支付。" <ref name="KFF"/>有450個醫療組織參加由CMS舉辦的"改善護理捆綁式支付計劃（Bundled Payments for Care Improvement）"（BPCI）。這項計劃試用捆綁式付款，作為提高品質和降低成本的方法。<ref name=mh>{{cite web| url=http://www.modernhealthcare.com/article/20130131/NEWS/301319949| title=More than 450 provider organizations join payment-bundling initiative| author=Jessica Zigmond| date=January 31, 2013| publisher=Modern Healthcare| access-date=June 13, 2016| archive-date=2014-08-30| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140830183729/http://www.modernhealthcare.com/article/20130131/NEWS/301319949| dead-url=no}}</ref>CMS在2016年6月宣布，這項計劃會再延長兩年。<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.acc.org/latest-in-cardiology/articles/2016/06/10/11/12/business-consult| title=Business Consult: CMS is Upping its Bet on Bundled Payments Deirdre Baggot, PhD, MBA, RN, Former Expert Reviewer, Bundled Payments for Care Improvement Initiative at CMS Former Lead, CMS Acute Care Episode (ACE) Demonstration Principal, ECG Management Consultants| date=June 1, 2016| publisher=American College of Cardiology| access-date=August 18, 2016| archive-date=2021-01-21| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210121044944/https://www.acc.org/latest-in-cardiology/articles/2016/06/10/11/12/business-consult| dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
2015年7月，CMS宣布一項提議，要求強制實行包含出院後90天費用的捆綁支付模式，作為Medicare受益人接受[[關節置換手術|關節置換手術]]（稱為“關節置換全面護理計劃”）新的計劃。這項計劃源自2011年啟動的“捆綁式付款照護服務改善計劃”以及在“Medicare急性病症護理示範項目”的研究。這項計劃將把成本效率、患者治療結果、以及提供者之間的協調都提高。捆綁式付款會把不必要的測試和治療的需求消除。<ref name="#1">{{cite journal| journal=Healthcare Financial Management: Journal of the Healthcare Financial Management Association| date=October 1, 2015|author1=Deirdre Baggot |author2=Andy Edeburn | title=Mandated Bundled Payments Compel Hospitals to Rethink Post-Acute Care}}</ref>2016年7月，CMS宣布三個新的捆綁式付款，稱為疾病發作治療支付模型（episode payment models，EPMs），用於心血管護理療程（包括急性[[心肌梗死|心肌梗塞]]（AMI））、心臟繞道手術（CABG）、和{{link-en|髖部骨折|femoral fracture}}手術。新的支付模式於2017年7月1日生效。<ref name="#1"/> 由於[[唐納·川普|川普]]總統的原因，執行的規模有所縮減，有部分支付模式的生效日期也被推遲。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dicardiology.com/article/cms-cancel-mandatory-cardiac-bundled-payments-and-cardiac-rehabilitation-payment-model |title=存档副本 |access-date=2020-09-11 |archive-date=2019-11-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191120134948/https://www.dicardiology.com/article/cms-cancel-mandatory-cardiac-bundled-payments-and-cardiac-rehabilitation-payment-model |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==優點==
捆綁式付款提倡者認為這種方式的優點有：

*25％到30％的療程受到浪費，無助於提高護理品質。<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.npr.org/sections/money/2013/11/27/247531043/hospital-puts-docs-on-the-spot-to-lower-costs| title=Hospital Puts Docs On the Spot to Lower Costs| date=November 27, 2013| author=Lisa Chow| publisher=NPR| access-date=June 13, 2016| archive-date=2021-01-30| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210130075723/https://www.npr.org/sections/money/2013/11/27/247531043/hospital-puts-docs-on-the-spot-to-lower-costs| dead-url=no}}</ref>捆綁式付款與[[按服務收費|按服務收費]]不同，可阻攔[[不必要的醫療衛生|不必要的醫療衛生]]，鼓勵各服務提供者之間的協調，並提高品質。<ref name="Miller-2009"/><ref name=cg2>{{cite web| url=http://www.thecamdengroup.com/thought-leadership/top-ten/bundled-payments-revisited-10-new-critical-success-factors/| title=Bundled Payments Revisited: 10 New Critical Success Factors| date=April 2011| author=Deirdre Baggot| publisher=GE Healthcare Camden Group| access-date=June 13, 2016| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160617055436/http://www.thecamdengroup.com/thought-leadership/top-ten/bundled-payments-revisited-10-new-critical-success-factors/| archive-date=June 17, 2016| url-status=dead}}</ref>
*捆綁式付款與論人計酬支付不同，不會因提供者給予重症者護理，而受到財務上的懲罰。<ref name="Miller-2009"/>
*在比較過按服務收費、{{link-en|按績效計算報酬|Pay for performance (healthcare)}}、捆綁式支付、以及論人計酬支付（通用支付）的優缺點，由Robert E Mechanic和Stuart H Altman兩位撰寫報告中的結論是"捆綁式支付是最直接可行的方法。"<ref name="Mechanic-2009">{{Cite journal | vauthors = Mechanic RE, Altman SH | title = Payment reform options: episode payment is a good place to start | journal = Health Aff (Millwood) | volume = 28 | issue = 2 | pages = w262-71 | year = 2009 | doi = 10.1377/hlthaff.28.2.w262 | url = http://content.healthaffairs.org/cgi/content/full/28/2/w262 | pmid = 19174388 | doi-access = free | access-date = 2020-09-11 | archive-date = 2010-10-22 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101022161812/http://content.healthaffairs.org/cgi/content/full/28/2/w262 | dead-url = no }}</ref>
*美國智庫[[蘭德公司|蘭德公司]]的研究人員估計，如果廣泛使用針對特定條件和程序的捆綁式支付的PROMETHEUS模式，"2010年至2019年間，全國醫療衛生支出可減少5.4％"。<ref name="Hussey-2009">{{Cite journal| vauthors= Hussey PS, Eibner C, Ridgely MS, McGlynn EA | title = Controlling U.S. health care spending--separating promising from unpromising approaches | journal = N Engl J Med | volume = 361 | issue = 22 | pages = 2109–11 | year = 2009 | doi = 10.1056/NEJMp0910315 | pmid = 19907037 }}</ref>這個數字比其他七個有關減少國家衛生支出的建議方法中所提到的都高。<ref name="Hussey-2009"/> 此外，蘭德公司發現，捆綁式付款可以降低消費者的財務風險，並可減少浪費。<ref name="RAND">{{Cite web |url= http://www.randcompare.org/policy-options/bundled-payment |author= RAND COMPARE (Comprehensive Assessment of Reform Efforts) |title= Overview of bundled payment |publisher= RAND Corporation |accessdate= 2010-03-13 |archive-date= 2010-12-29 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20101229210924/http://www.randcompare.org/policy-options/bundled-payment |dead-url= no }}</ref> 
*透過消除護理中的低效率和重複性-例如重複測試、不必要的醫療照顧、不足的術後護理，捆綁式支付為醫療機構和患者提供更多的好處。<ref name=cg2/>
*透過固定價格，以及發布成本和結果數據，這種付款方式對消費者而言有透明度。患者能夠根據事實作比較，而不是靠口耳相傳來做選擇。<ref name=cg2/>
*捆綁式支付還可促進規模經濟的產生，特別是如果提供者同意使用一種產品或同種醫療供應時，大家一起批量購買，通常可談出更好的價格。<ref>[http://www.physicianspractice.com/physician-compensation/bundled-payments-what-physicians-need-know "Bundled Payments: What Physicians Need to Know"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.physicianspractice.com/physician-compensation/bundled-payments-what-physicians-need-know |date=20170916165837 }} Shelly K. Schwartz, Physicians Practice, November 2012.</ref>

==注意事項==
在醫療機構選擇參與捆綁式支付前，他們需要用心研究適合此類報銷的護理案例。傳統上，醫師的品質監控和改善是由醫院的護理部門所管理。往捆綁式支付移轉，責任會轉回到醫生身上，因此在急診治療的執行以及重新調整戰略性的護理優先順序上思考，就很重要，這樣才能讓轉型成功。<ref name=cg/>一旦他們選出並把需要的護理方式定義後，他們應該：
 
*找出所有的相關成本
*列出疾病發作護理所需的各項服務
*估算護理費用如何得到補償
*確定有多少部門會參與補償的分配<ref>[http://www.aafp.org/online/en/home/publications/news/news-now/payment-special-report/20120921specrpt-paymentmodels.html "Taming Payment and Delivery Model Monsters"] Sheri Porter, AAFP News, September 2012.</ref>
*讓醫生參與護理協調
*創建護理執行模型，以減少浪費、減少冗餘、並改善提供者之間的溝通<ref name=cg>{{cite web| url=http://www.thecamdengroup.com/thought-leadership/top-ten/bundled-payments-ten-critical-success-factors/| title=Bundled Payments: Ten Critical Success Factors| date=September 2010| author=Deirdre Baggot| publisher=GE Healthcare Camden Group| access-date=June 13, 2016| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160617050900/http://www.thecamdengroup.com/thought-leadership/top-ten/bundled-payments-ten-critical-success-factors/| archive-date=June 17, 2016| url-status=dead}}</ref>
*找出在家庭護理選項做投資的優點<ref name=cg3/>
 
根據2018年2月刊載在月刊雜誌{{link-en|衛生事務|Health Affairs}}上的一篇文章，《政府作為創新催化劑：早期由聯邦醫療保險和聯邦醫療補助創新中心（CMMI）而來的經驗》，<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Government As Innovation Catalyst: Lessons From The Early Center For Medicare And Medicaid Innovation Models|journal=Health Affairs|volume=37|issue=2|pages=213–221|date=2018-05-18|doi=10.1377/hlthaff.2017.1109|last1=Perla|first1=Rocco J.|last2=Pham|first2=Hoangmai|last3=Gilfillan|first3=Richard|last4=Berwick|first4=Donald M.|last5=Baron|first5=Richard J.|last6=Lee|first6=Peter|last7=McCannon|first7=C. Joseph|last8=Progar|first8=Kevin|last9=Shrank|first9=William H.}}</ref>“[BPCI（捆綁式支付）]倡議還把實施此方法的商業和營運障礙凸顯出來。其中包括管理現金流量、為預期（而不是追溯）支付的程序制定預算、以及要對捆綁付款模式中提供者的加入做確實的追踪。召集組織（例如將多個提供者匯集以促成實施，有時召集組織必須承擔一些財務上的風險）可讓捆綁業務規模更快擴展，但由於引入付款人、召集人、和提供者的三方，會增加額外的複雜性。”
 
在案例研究方面：兩個大型學術中心在充血性[[心臟衰竭|心臟衰竭]]治療的提供和付款改革，<ref>{{Cite journal|date=2014-07-01|title=Case study: Delivery and payment reform in congestive heart failure at two large academic centers|journal=Healthcare|language=en|volume=2|issue=2|pages=107–112|doi=10.1016/j.hjdsi.2014.04.001|issn=2213-0764|last1=George|first1=Meaghan|last2=Bencic|first2=Sara|last3=Bleiberg|first3=Sarah|last4=Alawa|first4=Nawara|last5=Sanghavi|first5=Darshak|doi-access=free}}</ref>發表在2014年7月的季刊雜誌《醫療衛生：執行與創新（Healthcare: The Journal of Delivery Science and Innovation）》上，作者指出：“召集組織在下述方面有關鍵作用：提供技術的援助和施行的支援。臨床醫療領導者和衛生系統兩者不見得會擁有一套完整的付款改革工具。因此，由CMMI簽約而來的召集人在促進支付改革方面可發揮有效的功能。”
 
==設計選項==
實施捆綁式付款，可採用多種的形式。幾個關鍵的設計包括：

*預期付款與追溯付款：預期捆綁支付預先把固定價格支付給服務提供者，相對會獲得約定的服務。追溯捆綁一開始是用傳統的按服務收費方式付款給提供者；在護理結束後，如果收款的提供者實際發生的費用少於約定的的捆綁價格，可參與節約部分的分配，如果實際費用超過約定的捆綁價格，就超過的部分也要分攤成本。追溯付款有時被稱為"虛擬捆綁"。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ama-assn.org/ama/pub/advocacy/state-advocacy-arc/state-advocacy-campaigns/private-payer-reform/state-based-payment-reform/evaluating-payment-options/bundled-payments.page|title=Bundled Payments|website=www.ama-assn.org|access-date=2016-09-29|archive-date=2016-10-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161013211116/http://www.ama-assn.org/ama/pub/advocacy/state-advocacy-arc/state-advocacy-campaigns/private-payer-reform/state-based-payment-reform/evaluating-payment-options/bundled-payments.page|dead-url=no}}</ref>
*對訂價作風險調整：為反映患者病情的嚴重程度，捆綁式付款通常會使用風險調整因素來修改捆綁的價格。變化程度取決於使用哪些因素來做（例如根據患者過去一年的診斷結果、或是根據過去的三年的診斷結果、患者的用藥記錄）以及每種因素影響價格的程度。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://multimedia.3m.com/mws/media/885503O/3m-bundled-payment-ebook.pdf|title=Bundling payment for episodes of care: Balancing the financial risk of health care|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=3M Health Information Systems|access-date=|archive-date=2020-10-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201019221450/https://multimedia.3m.com/mws/media/885503O/3m-bundled-payment-ebook.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>
*風險分擔的程度：捆綁式付款可架構有“上行空間”（如果成本低於捆綁價格，則參與節約的分配），“下行空間”（如果成本高於捆綁價格，則需參與多出成本的分攤），或者上行及下行兩種均有。提供者可吃下所有的節省和/或超額成本（擔負100％的風險），或者他們可以承擔一部分風險，而由付款人承擔其餘的。
*除外部分，尾端風險和停損規則：捆綁式支付模型可建立保護措施，把提供者在極端情況下碰到的財務風險予以限缩。這些保障措施的形式有多種，包括排除某些類型的病例（例如有嚴重[[合併症|合併症]]的患者）的規則，排除超出成本門檻病例的費用（例如費用超過平均水準3個[[標準差|標準差]]的異常病例）的規則，停損規則則把提供者願意承擔的最高風險訂下，超過部分由付款人承擔。

==缺點==
捆綁式付款方式的缺點有：

*支持這種方式的科學證據被描述為"尚有不足"。<ref name="MA-2009a"/> 例如，蘭德公司研究的結論是這種方式對健康結果的影響是"尚不確定"。<ref name="RAND"/>
*它無法禁絕不必要的醫療衛生； <ref name="Miller-2009"/>例如，醫生可能會讓無需住院的患者住院。。<ref name="MedPAC-2008"/>
*提供者為求利潤最大化，可利用避免產生報銷金額不足的患者（例如，未按規定服用藥物的患者）、誇大疾病嚴重程度、給予低下的服務水準、在申請報銷截止日前不診斷併發症、或者將院後護理推遲到報銷截止日之後才實施。<ref name="Satin-2009"/><ref name="MedPAC-2008"/>
*醫院在患者住院期間，限制他們看專科醫生，以擴大醫院的利潤。<ref name="Galewitz-2009"/>
*由於提供者可能會將部分護理工作[[外包|外包]]給其他提供者，因此會在確定付款的分配上發生困難。<ref name="Satin-2009"/>
*例如，在確定公平的補償標準時，會發生行政和運營的成本。<ref name="Satin-2009"/><ref name="RAND"/>樣本小和數據不完整，都可能會導致難以算出適當的費率。<ref name="Robinson-2009">{{Cite journal| vauthors= Robinson JC, Williams T, Yanagihara D | title = Measurement of and reward for efficiency in California's pay-for-performance program. How the Integrated Healthcare Association discovered the problems of using 'episodes of care' as the basis for physician performance rewards | journal = Health Aff (Millwood) | volume = 28 | issue = 5 | pages = 1438–47 | year = 2009 | doi = 10.1377/hlthaff.28.5.1438 | pmid = 19738261 | url = https://escholarship.org/content/qt16b7r6dn/qt16b7r6dn.pdf?t=o9ng6l }}</ref>如果費率設置過高，提供者可能會提供不必要的服務；但設置過低時，則提供者可能會遇到財務困難，或者提供的護理不足。<ref name="Miller-2009"/>
*某些類型的疾病可能無法清楚的歸類為"疾病發作"。<ref name="MA-2009a"/>
*一個患者可能有多個相互重疊的捆綁。<ref name="Robinow-2010">{{Cite web |url= http://www.commonwealthfund.org/~/media/Files/Publications/Fund%20Report/2010/Feb/1373_Robinow_potential_global_payment.pdf |title= The potential of global payment: insights from the field |author= Robinow A |date= February 2010 |location= Washington, DC |publisher= The Commonwealth Fund |accessdate= 2010-03-13 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20100518051044/http://www.commonwealthfund.org/~/media/Files/Publications/Fund%20Report/2010/Feb/1373_Robinow_potential_global_payment.pdf |archive-date= 2010-05-18 |url-status= dead }}</ref>
*注重研究、教學、和新技術的學術衛生中心可能無法從這種付款方式受益。<ref name="Robinow-2010"/>
*提供者冒著巨大損失的風險，例如，如果患者在治療過程產生災難性的高額費用。<ref name="Guterman-2009">{{Cite journal | vauthors = Guterman S, Davis K, Schoenbaum S, Shih A | title = Using Medicare payment policy to transform the health system: a framework for improving performance | journal = Health Aff (Millwood) | volume = 28 | issue = 2 | pages = w238-50 | year = 2009 | doi = 10.1377/hlthaff.28.2.w238 | url = http://content.healthaffairs.org/cgi/content/full/28/2/w238 | pmid = 19174386 | doi-access = free | access-date = 2020-09-11 | archive-date = 2010-07-06 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100706085026/http://content.healthaffairs.org/cgi/content/full/28/2/w238 | dead-url = no }}</ref>有一個周全的"再保險機制"來說服提供者接受捆綁式付款，或許有所必要。<ref name="Guterman-2009"/>
*達特茅斯學院所屬的{{link-en|蓋塞爾醫學院|Geisel School of Medicine}}的一項研究顯示，美國各地的醫療衛生領域存在極大差異，報告將這種不一致之處歸因於缺乏標準化的護理方案。<ref name=cg2/>目前尚無全國統一認可的捆綁式付款方式，但預計業界將會繼續進行試驗，以進一步求得完善。<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.orhcnews.com/articles/08-2014/or-dbaggot-0814.php| title=The Bundled Payment Title Wave: Recap and Insight from the Fourth National Bundled Payment Summit| date=July 7, 2014| author=Deirdre Baggot| publisher=Oregon Healthcare News| access-date=June 13, 2016| archive-date=2017-02-02| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202000959/http://www.orhcnews.com/articles/08-2014/or-dbaggot-0814.php| dead-url=no}}</ref>

